  "title": "The Bone House",
  "description": "Welcome to Eugene Crowley's lecture: a deep dive on serial killers and the psychology of violence. The problem is, Crowley has a horrible secret. And time is running out. Immersive theatre at its finest, The Bone House explains exactly why we are addicted to spectacle... and why you can't look away.",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Marty Chan<br/><strong>Director</strong>: Grace Fitzgerald<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Sarah Dolman, Jarin Ten Hove, Jack Walker, Maya Wright<br/><strong>Designers</strong>: Grace Fitzgerald<br/><strong>Stage Manager</strong>: Amélia Boutin<br/>",
  "website": "https://www.instagram.com/stagedtheatreproductions",
  "plain_language": "Eugene Crowley is a lecturer who speaks on serial killers. He delivers a lecture to the audience with the help of his assistant, Jacob. Throughout the lecture, he reveals various secrets, and showcases his own weaknesses.",
